# ðŸ©¸ Anemia Detection AI (Leo Club Pilot)

### ðŸŒ Overview  
A **low-cost AI tool** to detect anemia from **phone photos of the conjunctiva** (inner eyelid).  
Piloted with **50 rural schoolgirls** via **Leo Club (Lions International)**.

> **Preliminary Result:** 88% agreement with lab hemoglobin in pilot (n=50).  
> _Not clinically validated. Research prototype._

---

### ðŸŽ¯ Objectives  
- Early, accessible anemia screening  
- Reduce school absenteeism  
- Empower community health workers  

---

### ðŸ§  Tech Stack  
- Python, OpenCV, TensorFlow  
- MobileNetV2 (transfer learning)  
- Runs on Android (future)  

---

### ðŸ“Š Pilot Impact (Self-Reported)
| Metric | Before | After |
|--------|--------|-------|
| School Absenteeism | 65% | **<40%** |
| Anemia Awareness | 20% | **85%** |
| Health Confidence | 30% | **90%** |

---

### ðŸ” How It Works  
1. Take photo of **inner lower eyelid**  
2. AI analyzes **color & texture**  
3. Get **risk score** in seconds  

