### ðŸ’» Demo Code (Placeholder)
```python
import cv2
import numpy as np

img = cv2.imread('eye_sample.jpg')
if img is None:
    print("Error: Image not found.")
else:
    redness = np.mean(img[:, :, 2])  # crude red channel
    risk = max(0, min(100, (255 - redness) * 0.8))
    print(f"Redness: {redness:.1f} â†’ Risk: {risk:.1f}% (SIMULATED)")<img width="1536" height="1024" alt="EFE64979-F05D-41A2-8284-6A5F59AFD3B7" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f9d921da-c4ae-40aa-93ff-83b33085c7a3" />

